text=>>recipeinfo%3c%3c%0aSummary: an `HTML5 skin using wiki pages to define page elements%0aVersion: 2012-09-15%0aPrerequisites: pmwiki-2.x%0aStatus: new%0aMaintainer: [[http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Profiles/Tamouse|tamouse]] %0aCategories: [[!Skins]]%0aUsers: {$Users} ([[{$FullName}-Users|view]] / [[{$FullName}-Users?action=edit|edit]])%0aDiscussion: [[{$Name}-Talk]]%0a>>%3c%3c%0a[[#desc]]%0a!! Description%0a(:Description {$:Summary}:){$Description}%0a%0a[[#install]]%0a!! Installation%0a%0a# Download Attach:mouse-skin.zip some place safe.%0a%0a# Create the mouse skin directory in @@pub/skins@@:[@%0a%0a  $ cd /path/to/pmwiki/pub/skins%0a  $ mkdir mouse%0a@]%0a%0a# Unzip the skin package:[@%0a%0a  $ cd mouse%0a  $ unzip /path/to/where/you/saved/mouse-skin.zip%0a@]%0a%0aAlternatively, get a clone of the git repository at [[http://git.gitorious.org/pmwikistuff/mouse-skin.git]]:[@%0a%0a  $ cd /path/to/pmwiki/pub/skins%0a  $ git clone http://git.gitorious.org/pmwikistuff/mouse-skin.git mouse%0a@]%0a%0a[[#config]]%0a!! Configuration%0a%0aAdd [@$Skin='mouse';@] to your ''local/config.php'' file to use this skin.%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#layout]]%0a!! Layout%0a%0aMouseSkin is ostensibly a fluid, 2-column theme, utilizing the %3caside> and %3carticle> `HTML5 tags to define the two areas.%0a%0aThe aside element is placed on the left hand side, as defined by [@%3c!--PageLeftFmt-->@], in a fixed position, so it will always remain visible while the user scrolls down the page. If the contents of the aside are longer than the viewport, it will scroll independently of the page.%0a%0aThe article element contains the following elements:%0a* page actions area, defined by [@%3c!--PageActionsFmt-->@], which is also in a fixed position at the top of the page, so the actions will always be available no matter where the user is on the page.%0a* header area, which is defined by a [@%3c!--PageHeaderFmt-->@] region%0a* page title area, defined by [@%3c!--PageTitleFmt-->@] region%0a* wiki text area, filled with [@%3c!--PageText-->@] region%0a* footer area, which is defined by a [@%3c!--PageFooterFmt-->@] region%0a%0a[[#usage]]%0a!! Usage%0a%0aMouseSkin uses the contents of various wiki pages in order to define page elements in the layout. Pages can come from either the current group, or the Site group.%0a%0a* [@%3c!--PageLeftFmt-->@] includes the [=SideBar=] page.%0a* [@%3c!--PageActionsFmt-->@] includes the [=PageActions=] page.%0a* [@%3c!--PageHeaderFmt-->@] includes the [=SiteHeader=] page.%0a* [@%3c!--PageTitleFmt-->@] includes the [=PageTitle=] page.%0a* [@%3c!--PageFooterFmt-->@] includes the [=SiteFooter=] page.%0a%0aDefaults for the above pages are included in the skin's wikilib.d directory (automatically bundled in the wiki page store).%0a%0aAdditional bundled pages which you can edit include:%0a* [=Site.SiteBrand=] -- used on the left side of the header to show page logo, wiki title and wiki tag. Included by [=Site.SiteHeader=].%0a* [=Site.SiteActions=] -- used on the right side of the header to show site-wide actions including the search box. Included by [=Site.SiteHeader=].%0a* [=Site.SiteNews=] -- included after the above two to display any site new or updates on every page.%0a* [=Site.GroupHeader=] -- basic stuff included before the wikitext is displayed.%0a* [=Site.GroupFooter=] -- basic stuff included after the wikitext is displayed.%0a%0aFor the [=Site.GroupHeader=] and [=Site.GroupFooter=] pages, you can follow the recommendations in [[Cookbook:AllGroupHeader]] recipe to use the Site's group header or footer all the time, or override with a Group's own group header or footer. (Note that setting @@$GroupHeaderFmt@@ or @@$GroupFooterFmt@@ in the skin.php would prevent it from being overridden in local/config.php.)%0a%0aTo use these, the simplest recommendation is the second alternative in [[Cookbook:AllGroupHeader]]:%0a%0a->[@%0a$GroupHeaderFmt =%0a  '(:include {$Group}.GroupHeader {$SiteGroup}.GroupHeader:)(:nl:)';%0a$GroupFooterFmt =%0a  '(:include {$Group}.GroupHeader {$SiteGroup}.GroupHeader:)(:nl:)';%0a@]%0a%0a[[#notes]]%0a!! Notes%0a%0a%0a[[#relnotes]]%0a!! Change log / Release notes%0a* 2012-09-15: Initial release.%0a%0a%25comment%25 If the recipe has multiple releases, then release notes can be placed here. Note that it's often easier for people to work with "release dates" instead of "version numbers".%0a%0a[[#seealso]]%0a!! See also%0a%0a%0a[[#contributors]]%0a!! Contributors%0a* [[http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/Profiles/Tamouse|tamouse]]%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a!! Comments%0aSee discussion at [[{$Name}-Talk]]%0a%0a[[#faq]]%0a>>faq display=none%3c%3c%0a%0aQ:%0aA:%0a
